    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-08-25T19:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-08-25T19:25:00-05:00" n="239"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <head>239. Circular Telegram From the Department of State to All African Posts<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d239fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1964–66, POL 23–9 THE
                        CONGO. Confidential. Drafted by Newsom, cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_OJL_1">O’Sullivan</persName>, and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_THJ_1">Tasca</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-08-25T20:25:00-04:00">August 25, 1964, 8:25 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>364. Department seriously concerned by reported broadcasts from Albertville
                    indicating Europeans held in city by rebel forces will be massacred if <gloss
                        target="#t_ANC_1">ANC</gloss> retakes city.</p>
                <p>This further substantiates earlier report that rebels under “General” <persName
                        corresp="#p_ONI_1">Olenga</persName> intend make hostages of Europeans in
                    Congo.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_USG_1">USG</gloss> believes such effort would reflect most
                    seriously on African image in America and Europe and critically affect ability
                    US and others exercise constructive influence in resolution Congo problem.</p>
                <p>If useful result can be expected desire recipient posts bring US concern this
                    report immediately to attention African Governments. Department requests Accra,
                    Lagos, Conakry, Addis, Khartoum make special effort encourage governments seek
                    ways not inconsistent with authority Central Government prevent any actions this
                    kind.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RDE_1">Rusk</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
